    "updated_at": "2015-11-26T20:00:57Z",
    "body": ":-1: I want to get this error when the file is not executable. Because it tells us that we shouldn't be executing it, and user needs to fix that. In Atom Linters we get a lot of cases with this error and 100% of them are when the user inputs an incorrect path as executable, We don't want it to chmod and magically try to execute it. It is an error and should be reported as an error.\n\nBesides, the behavior at the moment perfectly matches a terminal, we don't wanna diverge from it\n"
