    "created_at": "2015-11-27T01:50:29Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-11-27T01:59:47Z",
    "body": "@steelbrain I understand those arguments, however all execution permission information is lost when packaging in an `asar`. \n\nMy file _is_ executable before packaging, so the error that I'm getting is not expected to me and reveals an issue with electron (or `asar` specifically) since it's ignoring permissions I'm manually setting as a user, which is even more confusing.\n\nConsider the following example:\n\n``` sh\n$ mkdir asar_test\n$ touch asar_test/foo\n$ chmod 755 asar_test/foo\n$ ls -l asar_test/foo\n-rwxr-xr-x  1 jviotti  staff  0 Nov 26 21:54 asar_test/foo*\n$ asar pack asar_test app.asar\n$ asar extract app.asar output\n$ ls -l output/foo\n-rw-r--r--  1 jviotti  staff  0 Nov 26 21:57 asar_test/foo\n```\n\nI guess the real solution would be making `asar` keep all permissions when extracting out, but have no idea on how to tackle that, and just re-adding the execution permissions on `execFile` sounded like a reasonable default given that the user probably already expects the file to have execution permissions if attempting to `execFile` it.\n"
  },
